{"id":302,"date":"2020-08-26T20:37:50","date_gmt":"2020-08-26T19:37:50","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/www.russforster.co.uk\/?p=302"},"modified":"2020-08-26T21:18:39","modified_gmt":"2020-08-26T20:18:39","slug":"accessible-accordion-for-gutenberg","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.russforster.co.uk\/accessible-accordion-for-gutenberg\/","title":{"rendered":"An accessible accordion for Gutenberg."},"content":{"rendered":"\n<h2>The problem.<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>I was looking for a plugin that created an <em>accessible <\/em>accordion for Gutenberg editor considering its a common request for UI. I must have spent hours, days looking for 1, and I found a few&#8230;however, they all used the <code>&lt;details&gt;<\/code> and <code>&lt;summary&gt;<\/code> tag, which if you are in the know &#8211;<a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https:\/\/daverupert.com\/2019\/12\/why-details-is-not-an-accordion\/\" data-type=\"URL\" data-id=\"https:\/\/daverupert.com\/2019\/12\/why-details-is-not-an-accordion\/\" target=\"_blank\"> you know it&#8217;s not an accordion <\/a>.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-rf-blocks-library-accordion accordion-container\" id=\"accordion90\" data-allow-toggle=\"true\" data-allow-multiple=\"true\"><div class=\"accordion\"><span class=\"accordion-index\" style=\"display:none\">0<\/span><div class=\"accordion__heading\"><button aria-expanded=\"false\" class=\"accordion-trigger\" aria-controls=\"sectaccordion900\" id=\"accordionaccordion900id\"><span class=\"accordion-title accordion__title\">An accessible accordion, that was tough to find for Gutenberg.<span class=\"accordion-icon\"><\/span><\/span><\/button><\/div><div id=\"sectaccordion900\" role=\"region\" aria-labelledby=\"accordionaccordion900id\" class=\"accordion-panel\" hidden><div>I know that I have left the blue focus style, and some interesting style choices, but these are free to be modified at your discretion &#x1f44d;<\/div><\/div><\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>I searched and searched and each find was in my view not sufficient, even the <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https:\/\/github.com\/WordPress\/gutenberg\/issues\/21584\" data-type=\"URL\" data-id=\"https:\/\/github.com\/WordPress\/gutenberg\/issues\/21584\" target=\"_blank\">WordPress team are talking about it<\/a>, and they even suggest a &lt;details&gt; component. I think the Details HTML should be used, but not for the purpose of what it&#8217;s illustrating. Thankfully, they are launching their own as part of the Gutenberg editor which will be interesting to see.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2>If you can&#8217;t find it, develop your own.<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>I decided that I&#8217;d take the plunge and develop an actual accordion toggle, that uses the <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https:\/\/www.w3.org\/TR\/wai-aria-practices-1.1\/examples\/accordion\/accordion.html\" data-type=\"URL\" data-id=\"https:\/\/www.w3.org\/TR\/wai-aria-practices-1.1\/examples\/accordion\/accordion.html\" target=\"_blank\">WCAG accordion example<\/a>, so you know it&#8217;s accessible and to a good standard already.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Feel free to use it, fork it, clone it, but please <strong><em>don&#8217;t just copy it and say it&#8217;s your own work &#8211; contribute to it :)!<\/em><\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Download link<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/github.com\/rforster-dev\/gutenbergblock-accordion\" data-type=\"URL\" data-id=\"https:\/\/github.com\/rforster-dev\/gutenbergblock-accordion\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Download the gutenberg accordion plugin.<\/a><\/p>\n\n\n\n<div style=\"height:20px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"><\/div>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-pullquote\"><blockquote><p>I&#8217;ll write a tutorial soon on how I developed this.<\/p><\/blockquote><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Sharing a gutenberg block; accessible accordion.<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":0,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":[],"categories":[3,5,6],"tags":[],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.russforster.co.uk\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/302"}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.russforster.co.uk\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.russforster.co.uk\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.russforster.co.uk\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/1"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.russforster.co.uk\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=302"}],"version-history":[{"count":16,"href":"https:\/\/www.russforster.co.uk\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/302\/revisions"}],"predecessor-version":[{"id":324,"href":"https:\/\/www.russforster.co.uk\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/302\/revisions\/324"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.russforster.co.uk\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=302"}],"wp:term":[{"taxonomy":"category","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.russforster.co.uk\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/categories?post=302"},{"taxonomy":"post_tag","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.russforster.co.uk\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/tags?post=302"}],"curies":[{"name":"wp","href":"https:\/\/api.w.org\/{rel}","templated":true}]}}